- Usually I just say it.
- Oh, that would be very hard to recognize.
- Does that mean that you want the user to adapt to what a machine can do at the time and not what?
- Not necessarily, but this is a mutual approach.
I think that we will need to work in the near future, in particular, on the development of new sensor types, which will enable people to take a closer look at their reactions.
This can be laser sensors, for example, as they offer a good resolution at depth, which is very important.
- What demands do you make from your work with the Xbox Kinect sensors on modern cameras?
Is there a lack of resolution, depth or anything else?
- The current generation is basically a good starting point for our work in the field of three-dimensional recognition.
