There are also straps for the wrist that affect the nerve endings in the fingers, which is also a potential direction.
- Did you try to outdo the brain?
It makes you think it feels what it should feel when it just sees something?
- That's a good idea, so we haven't tried yet.
Here is another task that we will have to struggle with for a long time, namely to let a person who is physically in a closed room believe that he is instead in an open, virtually infinite space; here we work on concepts with treadmills (other than in gyms), mobile platforms and large balls.
