Hagman interpreted the role of Ewing as a corrupt, insatiable man with a charismatic smile: an insidious businessman and unfaithful husband who sought to instruct his alcoholic wife Sue Ellen (Linda Gray).
"I know what to say on J.R.'s tombstone," said Hagman in 1988.
